=== Auctions without suit agreement

==== After a jump rebid of hearts

When opener jump rebids hearts, then it's not possible to agree hearts
below game.
Therefore, #it is not possible to use kickback because it requires suit agreement.#

So 4NT is KC asking in hearts.

[%autowidth,cols="3*^,<",grid="none"]
|===
| 1H |  1S   | |
| 3H |  ?    | |
|    |  3S   | | forcing, [nobr]#trumps not agreed#
|    | 4C,4D | | natural
|    |  4S   | | to play
|    | !4NT! | | #KC for {H}#
|===

Note that opener's hand strength is fairly tightly defined so a natural
4NT is not needed.

